theorem
(X1 is (associative-ideal of X) implies X1 is (Ideal of X))
proof
assume A1: X1 is (associative-ideal of X);
A2: (for x,y being (Element of X) holds ((( x \ y ) in X1 & y in X1) implies x in X1))
proof
let x being (Element of X),y being (Element of X);
assume (( x \ y ) in X1 & y in X1);
then (( ( x \ y ) \ ( 0. X ) ) in X1 & ( y \ ( 0. X ) ) in X1) by BCIALG_1:2;
hence thesis by A1,CKB18:def 1;
end;
( 0. X ) in X1 by A1,CKB18:def 1;
hence thesis by A2,BCIALG_1:def 18;
